# Disable two checks that only fire on this codebase's deliberate style, never
# on real bugs:
#   bugprone-integer-division      - our grid-size macros are even (CHUNKW2 =
#                                     CHUNKW/2 = 32, REGW/2, ...), so the flagged
#                                     divisions are exact; used inside float
#                                     expressions they read as false positives.
#   readability-misleading-indentation - terse unbraced nested for-loops
#                                     (for(..)\nfor(..)\n\tbody;) are the house
#                                     style throughout; the code is correct.
# Leading '-' only removes these from clangd's default set; everything else stays.
Checks: '-bugprone-integer-division,-readability-misleading-indentation'
